  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to easily open and close commands panel.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: I find it difficult to close the commands panel. When I press command button `/` the button changes to send button. I'd expect it to stay the same unless I provide some command.   \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCommand button should not change to send button if I didn't provide any command.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36850088-1447321e-1d66-11e8-9a69-2ae9c20043d5.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36850036-f65018f2-1d65-11e8-85a8-278966cc7bb6.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSend button appears and in order to close the commands panel I need to click on the input field and erase the \"/\"\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to 1-1 chat\r\n- Click `/` to open commands. Now the only way to close it is by clearing the input field\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 1\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
